(11567, 963, '_background_image', 'field_56706beb9c8bf'),
(11568, 963, 'team_description', 'You shot a movie or youre about to make one.  You wrote a book. You have an event. A message. A product. Maybe all of the above.Now you need to sell.  A ticket, a book, an idea.  You want the right audiences.  Hmm, are you sitting down? As it happens, no ones waiting to hear from you. \r\n\r\nJournalists are busy and your potential consumers have infinite options.Media, meanwhile, is a supernova:  in a million pieces as the universe continues to expand. You want to go where the people are. Where they watch, read, think, engage . . . where they post, tweet, like, and stay in touch.\r\n\r\nWe can help you get there--where messages meet eyeballs, where goals meet bottom lines.'),
(11569, 963, '_team_description', 'field_58be339080008'),
(11570, 963, 'team_0_image', '907'),
(11571, 963, '_team_0_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11572, 963, 'team_0_name', 'Nancy Lovell'),
(11573, 963, '_team_0_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11574, 963, 'team_0_role', 'Partner'),
(11575, 963, '_team_0_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11576, 963, 'team_0_bio', 'A millennium, no, 15 years ago, Julie Fairchild and I separately went on our own and, since days alone can get long, thought we might share an office.  The physical office space never materialized, but inside a year, an LLP did.\r\n \r\nIn that company of two, I expected wed attract employees on their way to bigger things. What did I know? Our niche work is far more than widgets, and Lovell-Fairchild grew into an enviable team of professionals whom we\'ve seen grow into experts in what they do. \r\n \r\nIn our strategic-communications work, I lean into the communications part, urging our team, on one level, to spell canceled with one l, and, regardless of AP Stylebook, to use hopefully to mean what it says. More generally, in framing, messaging, media training, writing, pitches . . . I help shape client needs into news.'),
(11577, 963, '_team_0_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(11578, 963, 'team_1_image', '903'),
(11579, 963, '_team_1_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11580, 963, 'team_1_name', 'Julie Fairchild'),
(11581, 963, '_team_1_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11582, 963, 'team_1_role', 'Partner'),
(11583, 963, '_team_1_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11584, 963, 'team_1_bio', 'You tell your story, and I see it unfold in living color--including its potential to make the world a better place. Does that sound cheesy? My mom will tell you its in my DNA to look for what matters, poking and prodding for the right place to build a bridge between where you are and where you want to be. All the while, Im mentally skimming my Rolodex for new friends you need to know who complement your cause with theirs.  Im dogged (some say stubborn) and refuse to accept any result but the best. Because its your babyand we spread the word about goodness for a higher purpose.\r\n \r\nWhen not working, Im browsing an estate sale for treasures or enjoying my wildflowers in the Texas Hill Country with my chuck-wagon cooking husband, Rick, our four-grown children, and our ever-expanding family and friends, who keep me laughing.'),
(11585, 963, '_team_1_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(11586, 963, 'team_2_image', '906'),
(11587, 963, '_team_2_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11588, 963, 'team_2_name', 'Monique Sondag'),
(11589, 963, '_team_2_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11590, 963, 'team_2_role', 'Vice President of Operations'),
(11591, 963, '_team_2_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11592, 963, 'team_2_bio', 'I look at something and ask myself how I could organize it. Whether a spreadsheet, a kitchen pantry, or chapstick and candy bars at the checkout, my mind is trained to bring order. I was nine years old, at a friend\'s house to play, and instead organizing her closet. Her mom offered to take us to see a Disney movie. I passed on the ticket to continue in my version of a playdate. \r\n\r\nA decade ago, I met Lovell and Fairchild. A decade later the conversation hasn\'t stopped. Lovell-Fairchild Communications has been a place to exercise all my organizational quirks from creating campaign flows, to orchestrating events of all sorts, to synchronizing the many plates that need to spin for any given project. My mission is to help people, clients and projects alike create white space to think and breathe. \r\n\r\nOtherwise you\'ll find me personally thinking, breathing, painting, cooking, reading, on the hunt for the perfect Old Fashioned, or spending time with people who make me laugh.'),
(11593, 963, '_team_2_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(11594, 963, 'team_3_image', '904'),
(11595, 963, '_team_3_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11596, 963, 'team_3_name', 'Lucas Fairchlid'),
(11597, 963, '_team_3_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11598, 963, 'team_3_role', 'Account Specialist'),
(11599, 963, '_team_3_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11600, 963, 'team_3_bio', 'I\'m marketing minded and prefer high-level strategizing over nit-picking details. I like strange situations that require fast thinking; I especially like new places and people, and getting to know them well. My colleagues describe me as the companys Swiss Army Knife, but Id say Im a bridger of gapseven if theyre way outside my comfort zone--to connect people, make friends, and embrace uncertainties. \r\n\r\nChaos and adventure, I love, and spoken words over the written ones, especially self-written bios. I like hunting, fishing, hiking, kayaking, and anything outdoors. I love my wife, McLean, and the fraternal-twin boys she\'s carrying . . . arriving October-ish 2017. We have two crazy dogs, Hutch and Cricket. '),
(11601, 963, '_team_3_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(11602, 963, 'team_4_image', '905'),
(11603, 963, '_team_4_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11604, 963, 'team_4_name', 'Michael Conrad'),
(11605, 963, '_team_4_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11606, 963, 'team_4_role', 'Media Specialist'),
(11607, 963, '_team_4_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11608, 963, 'team_4_bio', 'The art of publicity is a black art; but it has come to stay, and every year adds to its potency.  Thomas Paine\r\n\r\nLet\'s face it, our world is deluded with all the worst kinds of publicity. The proof is in a quick Google search of today\'s top stories, and frankly, I want no part of that. Having worked with the smallest outlets in North Dakota, to the largest platforms in New York, my passion is to take your best story and tell it to the right media. When those two things come together, we have a real chance of influencing the 24-hour news cycle for the better and making a difference. \r\n\r\nWhen I\'m not practicing the dark arts of PR, you\'ll find me with my beautiful family (Lindy, John Alfred, Clementine), playing the fiddle, making espresso, or making things out of wood. '),
(11609, 963, '_team_4_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(11610, 963, 'team_5_image', '902'),
(11611, 963, '_team_5_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11612, 963, 'team_5_name', 'Catherine Binkley'),
(11613, 963, '_team_5_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11614, 963, 'team_5_role', 'Operations'),
(11615, 963, '_team_5_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11616, 963, 'team_5_bio', 'I love people, words and stories. Especially the ones that change lives. Details and checklists are my MO. I like to talk, and I love to listen. Relationships are essential to my being. Its likely I wont forget you, and when theres a story you need to hear, Ill make sure to send it your way. \r\n \r\nMarketing, journalism, and all of the above passions collide in my role at Lovell-Fairchild.  Knowing our clients and their stories, connecting them with media who want audiences to be touched in a positive way, and watching the chemistry take place is pure joy. Logistics, details and accurate expense reports are the icing on the cake.\r\n \r\nWhen Im away from my computer, youll find me running with my two black labs and toddler, eating frozen yogurt with my husband, or hanging out on a picnic under the Washington Monument. '),
(11617, 963, '_team_5_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(11618, 963, 'team_6_image', '908'),
(11619, 963, '_team_6_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
(11620, 963, 'team_6_name', 'Paul Cozby'),
(11621, 963, '_team_6_name', 'field_58be26f1d5a68'),
(11622, 963, 'team_6_role', 'Senior Associate'),
(11623, 963, '_team_6_role', 'field_58be26f8d5a69'),
(11624, 963, 'team_6_bio', 'I\'m a Texan by birth, a New Yorker by choice, and proud of both. After two careers in newspapers and corporate PR, I moved to NYC (with a very understanding wife) in 2006 to write musicals. (Our five kids refer to it as "Dad\'s midlife crisis.")  In 2008, my longtime friend Nancy Lovell called with a little writing "jobbie," and I\'ve had the great privilege of writing for Nancy and Julie almost daily since. I\'m motivated to tell good stories for L-F clients that help our team gain positive, engaging exposure for them. I enjoy guiding our materials through the editing process to get the best press pieces we can. And I love working with the L-F family.'),
