(12623, 983, '_team', 'field_58be26c7d5a66'),
(12624, 983, 'team_description', 'You shot a movie or youre about to make one.  You wrote a book. You have an event. A message. A product. Maybe all of the above.Now you need to sell.  A ticket, a book, an idea.  You want the right audiences.  Hmm, are you sitting down? As it happens, no ones waiting to hear from you. \r\n\r\nJournalists are busy and your potential consumers have infinite options.Media, meanwhile, is a supernova:  in a million pieces as the universe continues to expand. You want to go where the people are. Where they watch, read, think, engage . . . where they post, tweet, like, and stay in touch.\r\n\r\nWe can help you get there--where messages meet eyeballs, where goals meet bottom lines.'),
(12625, 983, '_team_description', 'field_58be339080008'),
(12626, 983, 'team_0_bio', 'A millennium, no, 15 years ago, Julie Fairchild and I separately went on our own and, since days alone can get long, thought we might share an office.  The physical office space never materialized, but inside a year, an LLP did.\r\n \r\nIn that company of two, I expected wed attract employees on their way to bigger things. What did I know? Our niche work is far more than widgets, and Lovell-Fairchild grew into an enviable team of professionals whom we\'ve seen grow into experts in what they do. \r\n \r\nIn our strategic-communications work, I lean into the communications part, urging our team, on one level, to spell canceled with one l, and, regardless of AP Stylebook, to use hopefully to mean what it says. More generally, in framing, messaging, media training, writing, pitches . . . I help shape client needs into news.'),
