(359, 1, '2017-04-14 18:07:24', '2017-04-14 18:07:24', 'Caleb Hogan has grown up understanding the importance of stating his case, backing it with facts, and choosing what\'s right ... come what may.\r\n\r\nIt has served him well to this point, but has it prepared him to deal with the most important legal issue of our time: When does life really begin?\r\n\r\nIn preparation for the National Moot Court championship, Caleb must decideand argue forwhat he truly believes. And wherever he lands will have consequences.\r\n\r\nIf he takes the pro-life argument, he stands to lose the most important competition of his lifeand the support of his mother, a high-profile lawyer. If he follows his mother\'s lead, he could win the coveted title ... but lose the heart of his teammate Rachel in the process.\r\n\r\nWhile compromise might be the easiest solution, it could also be the most dangerous. Come What May is a vivid reminder that choosing what\'s right is never easy ... but it\'s always worth the cost.\r\n\r\nCome What May is the first film produced by the Advent Film Group, which is committed to training up the next generation of filmmakers.', 'Come What May', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'come-what-may__trashed', '', '', '2017-07-12 18:03:45', '2017-07-12 18:03:45', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=359', 40, 'clients', '', 0),
