(427, 1, '2017-04-14 22:13:12', '2017-04-14 22:13:12', 'On the social ravages of disappearing fathers\r\n\r\nDoug Stringer-author, speaker, and humanitarian-holds a Ph.D. in Leadership and Human Development. He founded Turning Point Ministries. He\'s built an international movement known as Somebody Cares, spurring grassroots response to community crises including devastation from natural disasters, poverty, homelessness and more.\r\n\r\nTo the point of his work these days, Doug Stringer grew up without a father. The author of the new "Hope for a Fatherless Generation" and the classic "Who\'s Your Daddy Now?" is a rising voice, ringing the alarm about the overwhelming epidemic, the individual and cultural consequences of a society overflowing with fatherless boys and girls, men and women. But Doug\'s message is not all grim. He encourages Christian men to step up as spiritual fathers to the fatherless.\r\n\r\n<b>Topics:</b>\r\nCauses, effects, and recovery from MIA fathers\r\nDisaster relief and humanitarian aid\r\n\r\n<b>Interviews:</b>\r\nDoug Stringer-author, leader, activist,humanitarian', 'Somebody Cares America', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'somebody-cares-america', '', '', '2017-07-12 16:34:30', '2017-07-12 16:34:30', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=427', 138, 'clients', '', 0),
