(431, 1, '2017-04-14 22:33:27', '2017-04-14 22:33:27', 'BIBLICAL EPIC \'RISEN\' Red-Carpet Event\r\n\r\nDallas Monday, Feb. 15\r\n\r\nA ROMAN TRIBUNE MUST PROVE\r\n\r\nTHE RESURRECTION IS A HOAX\r\n\r\nFilmgoers Meet Joseph Fiennes, Producers\r\n\r\nWHAT:\r\n\r\nRed-carpet screening and media junket with RISEN star Joseph Fiennes (SHAKESPEARE IN LOVE), Sony Affirm Vice President Rich Peluso and RISEN Producers Mickey Liddell and Pete Shilaimon.\r\n\r\nWHERE:\r\n\r\nDallas\' Highland Park Village Theater\r\n\r\nHighland Park Village, 32 Highland Park Village\r\n\r\nDallas 75205\r\n\r\nWHEN:\r\n\r\n3:30 p.m. - Media screening (media interviewers must see film first)\r\n\r\n5:30 p.m. - Open red carpet for public photos\r\n\r\n6:00 p.m. - Media photo ops and red-carpet interviews\r\n\r\n7:00 p.m. - Press junket during screening\r\n\r\nPost-film - Moviegoers hear from moviemakers\r\n\r\nReception\r\n\r\nVisit', 'Risen - Dallas Red-Carpet Premiere', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'risen-dallas-red-carpet-premiere', '', '', '2017-07-12 16:34:30', '2017-07-12 16:34:30', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=431', 127, 'clients', '', 0),
(432, 1, '2017-04-14 22:35:19', '2017-04-14 22:35:19', 'HOUSTON-BASED STORY, BESTSELLING BOOK--NOW A\r\nNATIONAL MOVIE--OPENS WITH HOUSTON HOMECOMING\r\n\'90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN\' Premieres Sept. 11\r\nThe Real Don &amp; Eva Piper Celebrate with More "Real" People from the Film\r\n90MinutesinHeaventheMovie.com\r\nWHAT\r\nThe gripping Houston-based story that sold 7 million books--starting with a car crash outside Huntsville, Texas--is a new movie starring Hayden Christensen (STAR WARS, JUMPER) and Kate Bosworth (BLUE CRUSH, SUPERMAN RETURNS). On Sept. 11, the red-carpet premiere of 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN comes home--to the AMC Gulf Pointe 30--as author Don Piper and his wife, Eva, and many people from the real story, kick off the nationwide theatrical debut of the movie about Dons death and life.\r\n\r\nWHO\r\nHouston red carpet for 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN features the Piper familyDon, Eva, Nicole, Chris and Joe, along with the real Cliff McArdle (played by Michael W. Smith), David Gentiles (played by Jason Kennedy) siblings and daughter, Jay B. Perkins (played by Fred Dalton Thompson) son and granddaughter, Dick Onareckers (the pastor whose prayers brought Don back to life) wife, Anita WoodOnarecker, and church members past and present (many who served on Don Patrol).\r\n\r\nWHEN/WHERE\r\nFriday, Sept. 11Red Carpet/Premiere/Q&amp;A\r\nAMC Gulf Pointe 30\r\n11801 South Sam Houston Pkwy E\r\nHouston 77089\r\n\r\n5:00 p.m.Media check-in and reserved seating\r\n5:15 p.m.Invited guests red-carpet arrivals\r\n6:15 p.m.Red-carpet arrivals of Piper family\r\n7:00 p.m.Don Piper intro; 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN rolls\r\n9:10 p.m.Q&amp;A\r\n\r\nCONTACT\r\nFor press credentials to attend the red carpet, screening, and Q&amp;A, contact: Lucas Fairchild 214-577-9852lucas@lovell-fairchild.com or Monique Sondag 214-536-4319 monique@lovell-fairchild.com.\r\n\r\nSYNOPSIS\r\nDon Piper died Jan. 18, 1989, when a semi-tractor truck crushed his car. Declared dead by the first rescue workers to arrive on the scene, Dons body lay under a tarp for the next 90 minutes. His soul, meanwhile, experienced love, joy and life as hed never known before. Don was in Heaven.\r\n\r\nWhen another pastors prayers helped bring Don back to life, he became a living miracle. Yet this is one miracle Don wished never happened. Heavens bliss was replaced by excruciating pain and emotional turmoil. With the support and prayers of his beloved Eva, their three kids and friends near and far, Don clung to his faith in God and fought to regain a semblance of his previous life. The Piper familys incredible true story of perseverance and overcoming the challenges of lifeand deathbrings hope and encouragement to all who see it.\r\nStarring Hayden Christensen and Kate Bosworth, 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN is based on the inspiring New York Times bestseller with 7 million books sold. In theaters everywhere September 11, hope lives.\r\n\r\nNEWS HOOKS\r\n\r\nAn International Bestseller Comes Home to Houston\r\nNear I45 in Huntsville 26 years ago, in hard rain, a semi-tractor trailer hit Don Pipers car and killed him. Ninety minutes later he was alive again but facing 15 months at Hermann Hospital. What happened in those 90 minutes led to a runaway bestseller and, now, a national movie featuring Hayden Christensen and Kate Bosworth. On Sept. 11, the real people from the story will gather for its world premiere.\r\n\r\nWhat about Heaven Tourism Stories?\r\nThe Boy Who Came Back from Heaven recently came out as fabricated and publishers rushed to pull it. What about other accounts? 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN details Don Pipers immediate death from a head-on collision, his 90-minute visit to heaven and his return to a life of faith-shaking pain and physical rehab. And for years he kept the story to himself. Piper struck me as a reliable witness, Christianity Today editor Mark Galli wrote. Piper simply had the look and sound of sanity, of someone who was telling the truth, whose word was his bond. Talk to filmmakers about their focus on the true telling of an amazing story.\r\n\r\nGiving Films Gives Away the Profits\r\nWhen has a film company formed to send all profits to charities that help women and children? 90 MINUTES Producer Rick Jackson founded Giving Films to be a giving engine, and persuaded Don Piper to trust him to tell his story accurately.\r\n\r\nFor interviews, contact: Lucas Fairchild, Lucas@Lovell-Fairchild.com 214-577-9852 or Monique Sondag 214-536-4319 monique@lovell-fairchild.com.\r\n\r\nFor more about 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN, and for press materials, go to: Lovell-Fairchild.com\r\n\r\nAbout Giving Films\r\nGiving Films tells stories that reach faith-and-family film audiences through high-quality production and storytelling and open doors to wider audiences. All profits from Giving Films go to charity.\r\n\r\nAbout Samuel Goldwyn Films\r\nSamuel Goldwyn Films is a major independently owned and operated motion-picture company that develops, produces and distributes innovative feature films and documentaries, working with world-renowned and emerging writers and directors. Goldwyn is committed to filmed entertainment, offering original voices in uniquely told stories. SamuelGoldwynFilms.com', '90 Minutes In Heaven - Houston Premiere', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '90-minutes-in-heaven-houston-premiere', '', '', '2017-07-10 18:58:11', '2017-07-10 18:58:11', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=432', 8, 'clients', '', 0),
(433, 1, '2017-04-14 22:36:43', '2017-04-14 22:36:43', 'WORLD PREMIERE RED CARPET FOR\r\n\r\n\'90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN\' DRAWS STARS\r\n\r\nTO ATLANTA ON SEPT. 1\r\n\r\nIncredible True Story of Don Piper\'s Death and Return to Life;\r\n\r\nStars Hayden Christensen and Kate Bosworth to Appear\r\n\r\n90MinutesinHeaventheMovie.com\r\nWHAT\r\nThe world premiere and red carpet event for 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN heralds the Sept. 11 national debut of the stirring story of Don Piper, who died in a highway accident, experienced heaven, then returned to life with severe physical, emotional and spiritual challenges. 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN is based on Pipers New York Times bestseller of the same name, more than 7 million books sold.WHO\r\nThe red carpet for 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN features stars Hayden Christensen, Kate Bosworth, Michael W. Smith, Jason Kennedy and Tyler Smith; Producer Rick Jackson of Giving Films; and the Piper familyDon, Eva, Nicole, Chris and Joe.\r\nWHEN/WHERE\r\nTuesday, Sept. 1Red Carpet/Premiere/Q&amp;A\r\n\r\nFox Theater\r\n660 Peachtree St. NE\r\nAtlanta 30308\r\n\r\n5 p.m.Media check in and reserved seating\r\n5 p.m.General red-carpet arrivals\r\n6 p.m.Red-carpet arrivals of cast/crew\r\n7 p.m.Premiere of 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN\r\n9:05 p.m.Onstage Q&amp;A with cast/crew\r\n\r\nWednesday, Sept. 2Press Junket\r\nThe Georgian Terrace\r\n659 Peachtree St. NE\r\nAtlanta 30308\r\n\r\n8:30 a.m.Media check in for junket\r\n\r\n9 a.m.-1 p.m.Individual and roundtable interviews\r\n\r\nCONTACT\r\nFor press credentials to attend the red carpet, screening and press junket, contact: Monique Sondag 214-536-4319 monique@lovell-fairchild.com or Lucas Fairchild 214-577-9852 lucas@lovell-fairchild.com\r\n\r\nSYNOPSIS\r\nDon Piper died Jan. 18, 1989, when a semi-tractor truck crushed his car. Declared dead by the first rescue workers to arrive on the scene, Dons body lay under a tarp for the next 90 minutes. His soul, meanwhile, experienced love, joy and life as hed never known before. Don was in Heaven.\r\n\r\nWhen another pastors prayers helped bring Don back to life, he became a living miracle. Yet this is one miracle Don wished never happened. Heavens bliss was replaced by excruciating pain and emotional turmoil. With the support and prayers of his beloved Eva, their three kids and friends near and far, Don clung to his faith in God and fought to regain a semblance of his previous life. The Piper familys incredible true story of perseverance and overcoming the challenges of lifeand deathbrings hope and encouragement to all who see it.\r\n\r\nStarring Hayden Christensen and Kate Bosworth, 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN is based on the inspiring New York Times bestseller with 7 million books sold. In theaters everywhere this fall, hope lives.\r\n\r\nNEWS HOOKS\r\nWhat about Heaven Tourism Stories?\r\nThe Boy Who Came Back from Heaven recently came out as fabricated and publishers rushed to pull it. So what about other accounts? 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN details Don Pipers immediate death from a head-on collision, his 90-minute visit to heaven and his return to a life of faith-shaking pain and physical rehab. And for years he kept the story to himself. Piper struck me as a reliable witness, Christianity Today editor Mark Galli wrote. Piper simply had the look and sound of sanity, of someone who was telling the truth, whose word was his bond. Talk to filmmakers about their focus on the true telling of an amazing story.\r\n\r\nStars Align for Faith Films\r\nBooming star power and box-office numbers show the maturing faith-film genre. Talk to Hayden Christensen (STAR WARS, JUMPER) and Kate Bosworth (BLUE CRUSH, SUPERMAN RETURNS) on what attracted them to 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN.\r\n\r\nGiving Films Gives Away the Profits\r\nWhen has a film company formed to send all profits to charities that help women and children? 90 MINUTES Producer Rick Jackson founded Giving Films to be a giving engine. Ask Jackson Healthcares founder about his bold new philanthropy that begins with 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN\r\n\r\nFor interviews, contact: Michael Conrad, Michael@Lovell-Fairchild.com 214-616-0320\r\n\r\nFor more about 90 MINUTES IN HEAVEN, and for press materials, go to: Lovell-Fairchild.com\r\n\r\nAbout Giving Films\r\nGiving Films tells stories that reach faith-and-family film audiences through high-quality production and storytelling and open doors to wider audiences. All profits from Giving Films gof to charity.\r\n\r\nAbout Samuel Goldwyn Films\r\nSamuel Goldwyn Films is a major independently owned and operated motion-picture company that develops, produces and distributes innovative feature films and documentaries, working with world-renowned and emerging writers and directors. Goldwyn is committed to filmed entertainment, offering original voices in uniquely told stories. SamuelGoldwynFilms.com', '90 Minutes In Heaven - World Premiere Atlanta', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '90-minutes-in-heaven-world-premiere-atlanta', '', '', '2017-07-10 18:58:11', '2017-07-10 18:58:11', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=433', 11, 'clients', '', 0),
